{"article_id":"Js9AbTziBk3S7OEU","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The federal government has a \" powerful interest \" in a single , uniform definition of marriage ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"even if it excludes gay unions","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that are legal in individual states ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the lawyer","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"defending the federal Defense of Marriage Act","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"said Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"as the Supreme Court concluded two days of landmark arguments on gay marriage .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"But Paul D. Clement ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"hired by the House of Representatives","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to argue for DOMA","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"after the Obama administration refused to do so ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"faced often skeptical questions from the justices in nearly two hours of arguments","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"centering on the clash between the law ' s traditional definition of marriage between one man and one woman and a growing number of states","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that now sanction gay unions .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The justices , in particular key swing vote Justice Anthony M. Kennedy , seemed to be struggling with the impact","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that DOMA had in an area","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"traditionally reserved for the states .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"As several justices noted ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"the DOMA statute affects more than 1,100 federal laws , programs , taxes and benefits","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that differ for married and single people .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"The broad sweep of DOMA \" in our society means","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"that the federal government is intertwined with citizens ' day-to-day life , \"","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Justice Kennedy said .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"This puts the federal law \" at real risk","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"of running in conflict with what was always thought to be the essence of state police power ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"which is to regulate marriage , divorce , custody . \"","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg added","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"for the federal government to tell legally married , same-sex couples","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"they ' re ineligible to file a joint tax return ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"take marital deduction","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"or have surviving-spouse Social Security benefits ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"\" One might well ask ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"what kind of marriage is this ? \"","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"The result ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"she said ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"would be \" two kinds of marriage :","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"the full marriage and then this sort of skim-milk marriage . \"","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"But as with Tuesday ' s equally dramatic arguments over California ' s Proposition 8 statute","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"that bans gay marriage ,","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"the justices gave no clear indication","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"of how they would rule on these gay marriage cases .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"And as in Tuesday ' s arguments , the justices spent a considerable amount of time","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"considering legal off-ramps","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"that would allow them not to decide the cases , or to issue a far less sweeping ruling","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"than many gay marriage advocates had hoped .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"LATEST UPDATES :","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Supreme Court weighs gay marriage , DOMA on second day","depth":4},{"id":49,"text":"The justices are expected to issue their rulings by June .","depth":5},{"id":50,"text":"The session again inspired colorful , sign-filled demonstrations for and against gay marriage on the plaza outside the Supreme Court building .","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"Alexandria lawyer Jim McDonald said","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"he would not oppose civil unions for same-sex couples , but not marriage :","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"whatever my wife and I are doing is not the same to what a homosexual couple does ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"whether they were involved in a wedding or not .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"I don ' t think","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"the word marriage is appropriate for the coupling of people of the same sex . \"","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"But Dalton Collins , a gay rights activist","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"studying law at the University of the District of Columbia ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"argued","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"that \" every American deserves to be treated equally under the law .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"... Justice is supposed to be blind . \"","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Wednesday ' s case , United States v. Edith Windsor , revolves around an estate tax bill","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"levied by the IRS against Ms. Windsor , now 83 , after the death of her lesbian partner .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Ms. Windsor was forced to pay $ 363,000 in federal estate taxes","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"because the government would not recognize her 2007 Canadian marriage to her late partner , Thea Spyer .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"Mr. Clement said","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"rationale behind the traditional marriage definition","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"approved overwhelmingly by Congress","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"and signed by President Clinton","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"was \" all","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"it has ever purported to be \" -","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"a definitional provision .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"\" When Congress passed every one of the 1,100 statutes","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"affected by DOMA ' s definition ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"the Congress","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"that was passing that statute","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"had in mind the traditional definition , \"","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"DOMA tells states","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"\" we ' re going to stick with what we ' ve always had ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"which is traditional definition \" of marriage ,","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"\" No state loses any benefits","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"by recognizing same-sex marriage .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"Things stay the same . \"","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"But it appeared that at least five justices","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"- Justice Kennedy and the court ' s four more liberal members -","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"had great difficulty","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"accepting Mr. Clement ' s line of reasoning ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"even as nine states and the District of Columbia have now legalized same-sex marriage .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"\" What gives the federal government the right","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"to be concerned at all with what the definition of marriage is ? \"","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"asked Justice Sonia Sotomayor .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Another issue","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"explored by justices","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"was the \" sea change \" in the popular attitudes about gay marriage since 1996 ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"and whether that was the result of the \" political effectiveness \" of gay-rights advocates .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Attorney Roberta Kaplan ,","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"representing Ms. Windsor ,","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"downplayed the influence of advocates .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"The nation ' s sea change on gay marriage is due to a \" societal understanding \"","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that came from places beyond political power of gay people ,","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. was skeptical :","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"\" As far as I can tell ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"political figures are falling over themselves","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"to endorse your side of the case . \"","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"The political-power question is important","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"because one of the tests","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"to give sexual orientation a heightened level of scrutiny","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"is that the group is politically powerless .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"The impetus for DOMA","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"- especially the extent of \" moral disapproval \"","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"noted in a 1996 House report","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"accompanying its debate on the measure -","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"was also examined .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"\" Is that what happened in 1996 ? \"","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"Justice Elena Kagan pointedly asked Mr. Clement .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Such language appears in the House report ,","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"he replied ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"\" and if that ' s enough","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"to invalidate the statute ,","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"then you should invalidate the statute .","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"But that has never been your approach . \"","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"Ms. Kaplan agreed","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"that \" moral disapproval \" was a factor in the 1996 vote","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"DOMA \" was enacted","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"to defend against the marriages of gay people , \"","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"when asked by Chief Justice Roberts","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"if she believed","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"that 84 senators","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"who voted for DOMA","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"based their vote on moral disapproval of gay people ,","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"she softened her response .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"\" I ' m not saying","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"it was animus or bigotry ;","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"I think","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"it was based on a misunderstanding of gay people . \"","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"Earlier in the session , the court queried Mr. Clement and two other attorneys on whether the Windsor case was properly before them ,","depth":5},{"id":144,"text":"and whether the House of Representatives had legal \" standing \"","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"to defend DOMA","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"in light of the Obama administration ' s refusal","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"to do so .","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"Mr. Clement argued","depth":6},{"id":149,"text":"that the House has historically had the ability","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"to defend its laws ,","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"especially when the executive branch declines to do so .","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"But court-invited amicus Harvard Law School professor Vicki C. Jackson said","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"the House of Representatives had no \" injury , \"","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"and the Obama administration wasn ' t asking the court to redress any injuries either .","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"\" There is no justiciable case before this court , \"","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"said Ms. Jackson ,","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"that it should \" await another case , another day","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"to decide this question . \"","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"Deputy Solicitor General Sri Srinivasan ,","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"arguing for the administration ,","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"said","depth":7},{"id":163,"text":"the high court should issue a ruling on DOMA ,","depth":7},{"id":164,"text":"and that there is precedent","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"for the executive branch to not defend a law","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"even while it was enforcing it .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"But Chief Justice Roberts challenged that line of argument ,","depth":6},{"id":168,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"the high court was being asked to do something \" totally unprecedented . \"","depth":7},{"id":170,"text":"Justice Kennedy also objected ,","depth":5},{"id":171,"text":"saying ,","depth":6},{"id":172,"text":"\" I ' m wondering","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"if we are living in this new world","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"where the attorney general can simply decide ,","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"' Yeah , it ' s unconstitutional ,","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"but it ' s not so unconstitutional","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"that I ' m not willing to enforce it . ' \"","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"After Wednesday ' s session , Ms. Windsor told reporters","depth":6},{"id":179,"text":"she thought","depth":7},{"id":180,"text":"the arguments over her case \" went beautifully . \"","depth":7},{"id":181,"text":"The justices took the case \" very seriously , \"","depth":7},{"id":182,"text":"she said ,","depth":7},{"id":183,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":184,"text":"that the session was a \" spectacular event for my life . \"","depth":7},{"id":185,"text":"Ms. Kaplan said","depth":6},{"id":186,"text":"she was \" hopeful \"","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"following the oral arguments ,","depth":8},{"id":188,"text":"and expressed skepticism","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"- as many legal observers have speculated -","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"the high court might avoid a sweeping decision .","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"The court \" has an obligation","depth":8},{"id":193,"text":"to decide \" such momentous legal and social questions ,","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"Ms. Kaplan told reporters ,","depth":7},{"id":195,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"she did not see evidence in the questioning","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"that the justices were shying away from a decision .","depth":8},{"id":198,"text":"Mr. Clement did not talk to reporters after the arguments .","depth":4},{"id":199,"text":"Ms. Windsor repeatedly remarked on the significance of the day ,","depth":6},{"id":200,"text":"noting","depth":7},{"id":201,"text":"that she still had not publicly revealed her sexuality","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"when she married her late partner .","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"\" I ' m talking to you guys freely , \"","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"she told reporters .","depth":7},{"id":205,"text":"\" I ' d have been hiding in the closet 10 years ago . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":411,"left":348,"right":410,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":348,"left":251,"right":347,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":243,"right":250,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":212,"right":242,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":211,"right":6,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":208,"right":210,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":0,"right":207,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":209,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":209,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":218,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":215,"right":217,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":215,"left":7,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":8,"right":213,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"